.TH eroosterctl-queue-flush 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-queue\-flush \- force retry of all failed queue entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl queue flush
.SH DESCRIPTION
Resets every queue entry with status \fBfailed\fR to \fBpending\fR with an
immediate \fInext_retry_at\fR. This is equivalent to running
\fBeroosterctl queue retry\fR for each failed entry individually.
.P
Use this after resolving a systemic issue (e.g., DNS misconfiguration, expired
TLS certificate on the outbound relay) to immediately reattempt all held
messages.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# How many entries are failed?
eroosterctl --output json queue list --status failed | jq length

# Flush them all
eroosterctl queue flush
# 12 entries flushed, 0 errors.
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
All entries successfully reset.
.TP
\fB1\fR
One or more entries could not be reset (database errors).
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\-retry\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\-list\fR(1)
